and, unfortunately, they may not be the last.

930
01:39:17,700 --> 01:39:20,900
The horrifying fact is that no one is safe,

931
01:39:21,100 --> 01:39:24,600
either in the planes above Dulles
or in the terminal below.

932
01:39:24,900 --> 01:39:29,800
The threat of a higher body count at the
airport hangs over the heads of everyone,

933
01:39:30,100 --> 01:39:33,800
and the holiday season of peace
and love has become a nightmare.

934
01:39:40,700 --> 01:39:46,300
Listen up, all units. I want
you to converge on hangar 11, all sides.

935
01:39:46,700 --> 01:39:48,700
This car, McClane. Get in!

936
01:39:49,000 --> 01:39:54,500
When the city blue show up with their
backup, they'll pick up the pieces. Move out!

937
01:39:55,800 --> 01:40:00,300
- McClane, say hi to my brother Vito.
- Merry Christmas.

938
01:40:01,300 --> 01:40:03,200
Hi.

939
01:40:08,400 --> 01:40:12,400
Goddamn it to hell! Move that piece of shit.

940
01:40:14,200 --> 01:40:16,800
Will you move that goddamn
piece of shit out of here?

941
01:40:17,000 --> 01:40:22,400
Vito, get the fuck out of the car
and get your ass in gear and help me!

942
01:40:26,700 --> 01:40:29,400
Hey, Coleman!

943
01:40:33,900 --> 01:40:36,300
- Hey, Coleman!
- Hi.

944
01:40:39,100 --> 01:40:42,800
...but at least the truth
is not among the hostages

945
01:40:43,100 --> 01:40:47,500
because I, Richard Thornberg,
just happened to be here

946
01:40:47,800 --> 01:40:54,100
to put his life and talent
on the line for humanity and country.

947
01:40:54,500 --> 01:40:56,600
If this should be my final broadcast...

948
01:40:59,400 --> 01:41:01,800
Amen to that, Dick.

949
01:41:03,000 --> 01:41:06,800
Dick? We're live, Dick. Where are you now?

950
01:41:10,800 --> 01:41:14,500
Truck lights approaching, sir.
They're here, right on schedule.

951
01:41:15,600 --> 01:41:17,600
The hangar door, open it.

952
01:41:18,200 --> 01:41:20,200
Clockwork.

953
01:41:42,700 --> 01:41:45,600
Jeez, you give me this story,
and I'll have your baby.

954
01:41:46,700 --> 01:41:48,700
Not the kind of ride I'm looking for.

955
01:42:00,800 --> 01:42:03,700
Colonel, if I may say so,
you are some piece of work.

956
01:42:03,900 --> 01:42:07,300
Thank you, Major. You're not so bad yourself.

957
01:42:07,600 --> 01:42:10,600
- Congratulations on your escape, sir.
- Thank you, Major.

958
01:42:10,800 --> 01:42:13,800
- You should save them until we are all safe.
- Sir.

959
01:42:14,000 --> 01:42:18,100
My congratulations, gentlemen.
You've won a victory for our way of life,

960
01:42:18,400 --> 01:42:22,000
my pride, my admiration,
and a kick-ass vacation.

961
01:42:22,400 --> 01:42:24,400
Now, get on board.

962
01:42:54,500 --> 01:42:57,000
- Ride too rough, cowboy?
- I don't like to fly.

963
01:42:57,200 --> 01:42:59,500
- So why are you here?
- I don't like to lose.

964
01:43:11,800 --> 01:43:15,600
I don't know about you, but I've seen
enough snow to last me a lifetime.

965
01:43:15,900 --> 01:43:21,100
- You don't get much of that in the tropics.
- For you gentlemen, we'll import it.

966
01:43:23,400 --> 01:43:25,700
Shit. They left the hangar.

967
01:43:28,900 --> 01:43:30,900
Right there. Get that.

968
01:43:31,200 --> 01:43:33,200
- Now what?
- Get in front.

969
01:43:33,400 --> 01:43:35,400
Block their path so they can't get out.

970
01:43:35,600 --> 01:43:39,400
I'm not playing chicken with a 200-ton plane!
I'm crazy, but not that crazy.

971
01:43:39,600 --> 01:43:43,400
- Dulles, this is Northeast 140.
- That's Holly's plane.

972
01:43:43,700 --> 01:43:46,000
Request emergency clearance.

973
01:43:46,200 --> 01:43:48,500
I know you won't answer but you better listen.

974
01:43:48,700 --> 01:43:53,500
We're down to fumes and we have to land.
In five minutes, we're coming in.

975
01:43:53,800 --> 01:43:58,800
- That's my wife's plane. Take it fuckin' down!
- I'm not getting in front of that plane.

976
01:44:03,400 --> 01:44:05,300
How about gettin' over top of it?

977
01:44:05,800 --> 01:44:08,100
This is the captain. Your attention.

978
01:44:08,300 --> 01:44:11,500
We have no choice
but to attempt an emergency landing.

979
01:44:11,800 --> 01:44:14,800
Fasten your seat belts
and assume crash positions,

980
01:44:15,000 --> 01:44:19,300
- as instructed by your cabin attendants.
- Let's have the emergency check list.

981
01:44:19,600 --> 01:44:23,400
Attention, all air traffic in Dulles area.
This is Northeast 140.

982
01:44:23,600 --> 01:44:26,100
We are attempting an emergency landing.

983
01:44:31,400 --> 01:44:33,600
I don't wanna die.

984
01:44:34,200 --> 01:44:36,100
I'm sorry.

985
01:44:39,100 --> 01:44:41,100
God!

986
01:44:50,100 --> 01:44:52,500
Thy rod and thy staff they comfort me.

987
01:44:59,500 --> 01:45:02,300
- Hang on!
- What are you doing?

988
01:45:02,500 --> 01:45:07,300
You wanted a story.
Nice and easy, boys. Get me in low.

989
01:45:11,200 --> 01:45:15,400
- Bring me down.
- You'll get yourself killed.

990
01:45:22,300 --> 01:45:24,800
Bring it in low. Keep over the wing.

991
01:45:32,700 --> 01:45:34,700
Lower.

992
01:45:43,500 --> 01:45:46,900
John, what the fuck are you doin'
out on the wing of this plane?

993
01:45:54,900 --> 01:45:56,500
Damn!

994
01:46:03,000 --> 01:46:05,400
There's something wrong.

995
01:46:05,600 --> 01:46:08,000
The ailerons. We can't take off.

996
01:46:14,300 --> 01:46:16,400
It's McClane again.

997
01:46:16,600 --> 01:46:18,800
Son of a bitch!

998
01:46:20,100 --> 01:46:23,200
- I'll do him.
- This time, do it right.

999
01:46:23,500 --> 01:46:26,700
Just get us in the air, General.
You're the only man who can do it.

1000
01:46:26,900 --> 01:46:30,200
Don't shoot. That wing is fully fuelled.

1001
01:47:21,500 --> 01:47:24,100
Too bad, McClane. I kinda liked you.

1002
01:47:32,300 --> 01:47:34,300
I got enough friends.

1003
01:48:13,000 --> 01:48:15,200
Time for the main event.

1004
01:48:50,300 --> 01:48:52,300
You motherfucker!

1005
01:49:04,100 --> 01:49:06,100
How's it goin'?

1006
01:49:17,700 --> 01:49:20,000
Happy landings, asshole!

1007
01:50:11,200 --> 01:50:13,100
Yippee-ki-yay, motherfucker.

1008
01:51:05,100 --> 01:51:07,200
Holly!

1009
01:51:07,500 --> 01:51:09,700
Here's your fuckin' landing light.

1010
01:51:22,100 --> 01:51:25,500
Look! I see it.

1011
01:51:51,400 --> 01:51:53,600
They used the fuckin' fire to see.

1012
01:51:53,800 --> 01:51:56,500
They can all do that. Let's tell 'em.

1013
01:51:56,700 --> 01:51:59,700
They already know. Listen.

1014
01:52:00,000 --> 01:52:03,600
They're using the fire trail as a guide.
If they can do it, so can we.

1015
01:52:22,600 --> 01:52:25,200
Any landing you can walk
away from is a good one.

1016
01:53:37,300 --> 01:53:39,800
Holly!

1017
01:54:27,500 --> 01:54:29,800
Oh, God. Oh, baby.

1018
01:54:30,300 --> 01:54:34,500
- I thought I was never gonna see you again.
- That's what I thought about you.

1019
01:54:35,000 --> 01:54:37,000
I love you so much.

1020
01:54:40,800 --> 01:54:43,600
They told me there were
terrorists at the airport.

1021
01:54:43,800 --> 01:54:46,500
Yeah. I heard that, too.

1022
01:54:54,400 --> 01:54:56,500
God, that's beautiful.

1023
01:54:59,600 --> 01:55:01,600
Yup. It sure is.

1024
01:55:04,000 --> 01:55:05,900
I love you so much.

1025
01:55:08,300 --> 01:55:12,500
John, why does this keep happening to us?

1026
01:55:18,800 --> 01:55:20,500
Let's go home.

1027
01:55:25,300 --> 01:55:27,400
Somebody help me, please.

1028
01:55:27,800 --> 01:55:29,900
Honey, help me up here, please.

1029
01:55:30,100 --> 01:55:32,100
Asshole!

1030
01:55:34,700 --> 01:55:37,600
Hey, officer, come on!

1031
01:55:39,200 --> 01:55:42,000
Hop on in here. Get your missus in.

1032
01:55:42,200 --> 01:55:44,000
What do you say, Marv?

1033
01:55:44,200 --> 01:55:47,100
I'll be damned if
I'm gonna clean up this mess.

1034
01:55:57,600 --> 01:56:00,600
You get this parking ticket
in front of my airport?

1035
01:56:02,000 --> 01:56:03,700
Yeah.

1036
01:56:04,300 --> 01:56:07,400
What the hell. It's Christmas.

1037
01:56:13,000 --> 01:56:14,700
Take off, Marv!
